\section{Page shell and shared helpers}

Using [[string.Template]] keeps the HTML easy to read without introducing a
separate templating engine.

The base page template also carries the viewport declaration.  Phone browsers
otherwise assume a desktop-sized layout viewport and shrink the whole page to
fit, which makes a polling form needlessly hard to read and tap.

