\section{Rendering question forms}

<<functions>>=


def _render_index(store: Store) -> str:
    items = []

    for entry in store.all_questions():
        items.append(
            "<li>"
            f'<a href="/{entry["url_prefix"]}"><code>{entry["url_prefix"]}</code></a> '
            f'{escape(entry["text"])} '
            f'(<a href="/{entry["url_prefix"]}/results">results</a>)'
            "</li>"
        )

    if not items:
        return "<p>No questions have been registered yet.</p>"

    return "<ul>" + "".join(items) + "</ul>"
@

The form renderer mirrors the parser's input policy.  Open questions keep both
the textarea and file picker visible because respondents may need a short note
plus an uploaded artifact.  The [[accept]] list is only a browser hint, but it
nudges the picker toward the text-like formats that [[_parse_multipart()]] can
actually decode and that the results page can show meaningfully.

Word-cloud questions render only the textarea --- no file picker and no
multipart encoding.  Pairing a free-text token with a file body would
not produce sensible cloud entries (the file body is either one giant
token or a fragmented mass of source-level identifiers), so the form
matches what the parser actually accepts.

<<functions>>=


def _render_form(store: Store, full_hash: str) -> str:
    question = store.question(full_hash)
    prefix = store.metadata(full_hash)["url_prefix"]

    if isinstance(question, MCQuestion):
        input_type = "checkbox" if question.multi else "radio"
        inputs = "".join(
            f'<label><input type="{input_type}" name="value" value="{index}"> '
            f"{escape(option)}</label>"
            for index, option in enumerate(question.options)
        )
        return (
            f"<p>{escape(question.text)}</p>"
            f'<form method="post" action="/{prefix}">{inputs}'
            "<button type=\"submit\">Submit</button></form>"
        )

    if isinstance(question, OpenQuestion):
        return (
            f"<p>{escape(question.text)}</p>"
            f'<form method="post" action="/{prefix}" '
            'enctype="multipart/form-data">'
            f'<textarea name="value" maxlength="{question.max_chars}"></textarea>'
            '<input type="file" name="file" '
            'accept="text/*,.txt,.md,.tex,.py,.rst,.csv,.json">'
            "<button type=\"submit\">Submit</button></form>"
        )

    if isinstance(question, WordCloudQuestion):
        return (
            f"<p>{escape(question.text)}</p>"
            f'<form method="post" action="/{prefix}">'
            f'<textarea name="value" '
            f'maxlength="{question.max_chars}"></textarea>'
            "<button type=\"submit\">Submit</button></form>"
        )

    inputs = "".join(
        f'<label><input type="radio" name="value" value="{value}"> '
        f"{value}</label>"
        for value in range(question.low, question.high + 1)
    )
    low_end_label = ""
    if question.low_label:
        low_end_label = f"<p>Low end: {escape(question.low_label)}</p>"
    high_end_label = ""
    if question.high_label:
        high_end_label = f"<p>High end: {escape(question.high_label)}</p>"

    return (
        f"<p>{escape(question.text)}</p>"
        + f'<form method="post" action="/{prefix}">'
        + low_end_label
        + inputs
        + high_end_label
        + "<button type=\"submit\">Submit</button></form>"
    )


@

